      • setHTML

        public static Main setHTML()
        Sets HTML mode. This uses tags for styling, and also prevents a system exit. This allows the code to be used for websites so as to not exit the web server process.
        Returns:
        the main instance.

      • cleanParameters

        public static void cleanParameters(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String[]> params,
                                   java.lang.String[] stringsIn,
                                   java.lang.String[] numbersIn)
        A utility escape quotes in named strings and sanitize numbers. All unnamed strings or numbers are deleted from the parameter map. Useful for handling servlet requests. Strings override numbers. Exact BCD financial numbers can possibly generate some imprecise double precision numbers.
        Parameters:
        params - the parameter map.
        stringsIn - the keys that strings are in.
        numbersIn - the keys that numbers are in.

      • filterPrintStream

        public static java.io.InputStream filterPrintStream(java.io.InputStream input,
                                                    java.lang.Class<? extends java.io.FilterOutputStream> clazz)
        Allows use of an output filtering stream on an input stream. Could be useful with chains and how input streams nicely match the data flow of parameters. Output streams as parameters require the equivalent of a process wait and join, whereas a fork can happen with no synchronization.
        Parameters:
        input - the input stream.
        clazz - the class of the filter output stream.
        Returns:
        an input stream to chain processing.
